    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-06-23T21:16:53+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-23T21:16:53+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-23T11:46:53Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-23T11:46:53Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system lingers about far western NSW, as a weak trough skims the southeast later today and into Wednesday morning. A new high will move across waters to the south on Wednesday and be centred over Tasmania on Thursday, as it continues to extend a ridge over SA on Friday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW010" description="West Coast" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-06-23T21:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-24T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-23T11:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-23T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Light winds.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-06-24T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-25T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-23T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-24T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Medium chance of showers west of Ceduna, slight chance elsewhere. Light winds. Overnight temperatures falling to between 4 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection not recommended, UV Index predicted to reach 2 [Low]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-06-25T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-26T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-24T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-25T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Streaky Bay. Slight chance of a shower. Light winds becoming northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h in the middle of the day then becoming light in the early afternoon. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 8 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 18.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-06-26T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-27T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-25T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-26T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">The chance of morning fog. Sunny afternoon. Winds east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h becoming light during the afternoon then becoming east to northeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 3 and 6 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="4" start-time-local="2026-06-27T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-06-28T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-06-26T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-06-27T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Slight chance of a shower west of Nullarbor, most likely in the evening. Near zero chance of rain elsewhere. Winds northeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to around 6 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
